    "attributes": {
        "action": "Grant amnesty and automatic ILR to under-18s after 5 years in the UK",
        "additional_details": "Currently, a young person could live for 10 years in the UK but be unable to claim ILR if there is a \u2018gap\u2019 period during those years when their parents couldn\u2019t afford to extend their visa or apply for ILR. This then \u2018resets\u2019 the 10 years\u2019 continuous residence that is required in order to apply for ILR, requiring them to wait at least 5 years before applying again. This should be changed.",
        "background": "The Government should automatically grant an amnesty to \u2018undocumented\u2019 children and young people under the age of 18 who have lived in the UK for 5 years, and give them Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR).",
